    "body": "Oh cool. This one is tricky because it refers to the libp2p RPC spec (RPC across the network for nodes to directly communicate) which is still being debated. \r\nI've written an initial version, and am not happy with it. The re-write will need to happen after I jig around with the rest of the networking. \r\n\r\nI'll let you know when its ready to re-implement. \r\n\r\nIn the meantime, we still need to write and define the standard RPC interface that links the node locally to the validator client. I'll have a look into that and make some clear issues surrounding it :)\r\n\r\n",
